SL, I’m really not sure what your point is with <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://216.239.37.104/search?q=cache:W8T01F6Asr8J:www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml%3Fxml%3D/news/2003/07/05/nguan05.xml+Britons+detained+in+Cuba+could+face+death+penalty&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF-8" target="top">this</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=%2Fnews%2F2003%2F05%2F24%2Fwcamp24.xml" target="top">this</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> article.  You are asking about WMD’s and how we would change from condemnation of this war to acceptance.  I don’t have the story saved (sorry, I just don’t) but I do remember quite clearly two trucks being found that turned out to be weather-metering devices used for filling and launching hydrogen balloons.  They were thought to be production plants at first, and later discredited. When I said false, I was referring to them.  Are you SURE these are not the same trucks?  I did notice your story is from 5-29, so the timing is right.<br>
